{
  "stem": "4963.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was like 2 o'clock in the morning and they rounded us up, and I, not having anybody there, decided, well-- again, my mind was very active-- I was going to throw myself into the bushes and escape.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I thought, well, when the people were all rounded up and taken to the headquarters that I was going to, you know, smuggle myself through.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Well unfortunately, one of the women-- our Jewish women and the transport-- said there was a child over there, so the Russians came looking through the bushes and found me and started beating me with his-- with his big pistol.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I thought that was already the end of me, and he thought so, too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he just left me in the bushes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because I was-- I had-- I did have a knapsack on me, and he was beating me on the knapsack.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So that kind of-- I escaped the heavy blows.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was wounded.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had-- you know, I was bleeding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had-- I had swellings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I wasn't-- you know, I wasn't-- nothing was broken.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I wasn't incapacitated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So, you know, when the Russian walked away, I just got myself-- picked myself up and threw myself back into the transport, you know, with the people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Schmuel was there and he kind of looked out for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we went to those headquarters and he says, no, we're-- we're not going to let you go.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were very prepared for them, because every transport had [NON-ENGLISH] and big watches that ticked-- I remember that-- and that's what the Russians liked.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, they-- they were very simple people-- the-- the policemen.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
